Package edu.ncsu.csc216.service_wolf.model.command

Class Command

  • java.lang.Object
    • edu.ncsu.csc216.service_wolf.model.command.Command
  • public class Command
extends java.lang.Object
    Command class encapsulates an Incident's transitions through the ServiceWolf FSM Each command has a CommandValue, which indicates which state an incident should transition to, commandInformation, which passes info such as the incident owner or updated status details, and commandMessage, which is just a message that gets added to the incident's message log
    Author:
    magolden

        public Command​(Command.CommandValue command,
               java.lang.String commandInformation,
               java.lang.String commandMessage)
        Creates a Command object with a command value, info, and a message
        Parameters:
        command - one of the enumerated CommandValue pseudo-object
        commandInformation - Command info such as reason for state change, owner, and developer
        commandMessage - Message given by command
        Throws:
        java.lang.IllegalArgumentException - with the message "CommandValue cannot be null" if the CommandValue is null
        java.lang.IllegalArgumentException - with the message "commandMessage cannot be null or empty" if the message is null or empty
        java.lang.IllegalArgumentException - with the message "commandInformation cannot be null or empty" if a command that needs commandInformation is null or empty
        java.lang.IllegalArgumentException - with the message "commandInformation should be null or empty" if a command that needs null commandInformation has data
